article.headline: Colgate 85, St. Francis (Pa.) 76
article.story: LORETTO, Pa. -- Pat Moore scored 25 points to lead Colgate to an 85-76 victory against St. Francis (Pa.) on Wednesday. Moore shot 9 of 13 from the floor, including 7 of 8 from 3-point range. Murphy Burnatowski (10 rebounds) and Damon Sherman-Newsome added 12 points each, and Luke Roh scored 11 for the Raiders (3-3). Umar Shannon had 24 points to lead the Red Flash (0-4), Stephon Mosley added 15, and Ronnie Drinnon and Dominique Major contributed 14 each. The Red Flash led 37-36 at the break in a back-and-forth game, but the Raiders went on a 14-2 run in the first 3:34 of the second half. St. Francis battled back and tied it at 68 with 5:56 left on Stephon Whyatt's made a layup, and Ronnie Drinnon tied it at 72-all at the 2:59 mark, but Colgate closed with a 13-4 burst for the final margin.
